gomodel:SYNGO_1474  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The primary PMID shows regulation of human PMCA3 activity, the inference shows the occurence of PMCA3 at the membrane of presynaptic terminals.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has 'calcium-transporting ATPase activity (GO:0005388)' and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'ATPase-coupled calcium ion transmembrane transporter activity involved in regulation of presynaptic cytosolic calcium levels (GO:1905056)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[Q64568] SynGO ID 87 (PMID:17183553, EM). Experimental description: HeLa cells were cultured in Dulbecco's-modified Eagle's Medium. p. 551" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2018-07-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1474" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

